![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

In `ResolveEncoding`, there are potential `NullReferenceException`s if `request.LoadFile` is null (since it has a public setter and could be set to null). Additionally, the comparison `!object.Equals(resolvedEncoding, Encoding.UTF8)` can be simplified and made more robust by comparing the `CodePage` property directly (UTF-8 code page is `65001` or `Encoding.UTF8.CodePage`). This avoids the overhead of `object.Equals` and is more idiomatic in .NET.

```c#
    private static Encoding ResolveEncoding(FileGenerationRequest request, LoadFileFormat format)
    {
        var loadFileConfig = request.LoadFile;
        var resolvedEncoding = EncodingHelper.GetEncodingOrDefault(loadFileConfig?.Encoding);

        if (format == LoadFileFormat.Opt)
        {
            bool isExplicit = loadFileConfig?.IsEncodingExplicit ?? false;
            return isExplicit || resolvedEncoding.CodePage != Encoding.UTF8.CodePage
                ? resolvedEncoding
                : EncodingHelper.GetEncoding("ANSI") ?? Encoding.UTF8;
        }

        return resolvedEncoding;
    }
